    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Everbuild sealant is best for bathrooms?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Forever White</strong> is Everbuild's dedicated sanitary sealant and the UK's best-selling bathroom silicone. It features C3 anti-mould technology that prevents black mould growth for up to 10 years. Use it around baths, showers, sinks and wet room installations. For a combined adhesive and sealant in wet areas, <strong>Stixall Extreme Power</strong> also works on wet surfaces.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between silicone sealant and polyurethane sealant?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Silicone sealants</strong> (like Everbuild Everflex range) remain flexible, are water-resistant and are ideal for sanitary, glazing and general sealing applications. They cannot be painted over. <strong>Polyurethane sealants</strong> offer stronger adhesion, can be painted, and are better suited for construction joints and floor sealing. Everbuild's hybrid range (like <strong>Stixall</strong> and <strong>EB25</strong>) combines the best of both \u2014 paintable, flexible, and strong-bonding.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are Everbuild sealants suitable for outdoor and weather-exposed applications?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Many Everbuild sealants are rated for exterior use and weather exposure. The <strong>Everflex 450 Builders Silicone</strong> is designed specifically for external applications including brickwork, roofing and cladding. The <strong>Black Jack range</strong> provides specialist bitumen-based products for roofs, gutters and below-ground waterproofing. Always check the product datasheet for specific UV and weather resistance ratings.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Everbuild products?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Everbuild range. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between Everbuild and Sika Everbuild?",
            "answer": "<p>Everbuild was acquired by <strong>Sika AG</strong> in 2013 and now trades as Sika Everbuild. The products remain the same \u2014 manufactured in the UK to the same formulations. The Sika backing provides additional R&D investment and quality assurance. All the trade favourites like <strong>Stixall, Pinkgrip, Forever White</strong> and <strong>Wonder Wipes</strong> continue under the Everbuild brand name.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Everbuild product should I use for bonding heavy materials?",
            "answer": "<p>For heavy-duty bonding, <strong>Stixall Extreme Power</strong> is the top choice \u2014 it bonds virtually any material to any material with exceptional grab strength. For rapid grab applications, <strong>Pinkgrip</strong> provides fast initial tack and is widely used for fixing skirting boards, architraves, dado rails and wall panels. Both are solvent-free and suitable for interior and exterior use.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
